# Frontend

Two products in one codebase. Admin: desktop-first, dense, professional. Ambassador: mobile-first, glanceable, motivating. Both: accessible, fast, beautiful.

## Routing

```
src/app/
  (marketing)/             — public pages, no auth (post-MVP)
  (auth)/                  — login, signup, recovery
  (admin)/[org_slug]/      — festival staff UI
    overview/
    leaderboard/
    analytics/
    ambassadors/
    content/
    tracklinks/
    sales-feed/
    rewards/
    challenges/
    opportunities/
    reports/
    settings/
  (ambassador)/[campaign_slug]?/   — ambassador PWA
    (or single-campaign default)
    home/
    share/
    stats/
    rewards/
    community/
    profile/
  r/[code]/                — edge redirector (separate runtime)
  api/                     — route handlers
```

Org context: subdomain (post-MVP) or `[org_slug]` path segment. Ambassador context: their active campaign (if multiple) is in a switcher or via path.

## Component library

Use shadcn/ui as the primitive layer (Button, Dialog, Form, Sheet, etc.). Build Ravo-specific composites on top:

```
src/components/
  ui/                     — shadcn/ui primitives (generated)
  primitives/             — small Ravo wrappers (RavoCard, RavoStat, etc.)
  charts/                 — Recharts wrappers with locked themes
  admin/                  — admin-only composites (LeaderboardTable, RewardRuleEditor, etc.)
  ambassador/             — ambassador-only composites (HomeFeed, ShareSheet, RewardTile, etc.)
  shared/                 — used in both (Avatar, EmptyState, ErrorBoundary, etc.)
```

Never import an admin component into the ambassador product or vice versa. Shared logic goes to `shared/` or to a hook in `src/lib/`.

## Theme

Dark theme matches the mockup: deep purple/black background, vibrant accents (purple, gold, magenta), white text. Light theme deferred to post-MVP. CSS variables in `src/styles/theme.css`. Tailwind config consumes the variables. Never hardcode hex values in components.

```css
:root {
  --ravo-bg: #0a0814;
  --ravo-surface: #14101f;
  --ravo-surface-elev: #1c1730;
  --ravo-accent: #8b5cf6;
  --ravo-accent-2: #fbbf24;
  /* ... */
}
```

## State management

- **Server state:** Supabase queries via TanStack Query. Cache key includes `org_id`. Invalidations are scoped.
- **Realtime:** Supabase Realtime → TanStack Query cache updates. Surfaced via a `useRealtime(channel)` hook.
- **UI state:** local `useState`. For complex flows (multi-step forms), use `useReducer` or Zustand store scoped to the route.
- **Forms:** react-hook-form + zod schemas. Schemas live next to the form in a `*.schema.ts` file.

No Redux. No global Zustand for everything. Local state by default; lift only when needed.

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements keyboard-accessible
- Color contrast ≥ 4.5:1 for text, ≥ 3:1 for large text and UI elements
- All form fields have visible labels (never placeholder-as-label)
- All buttons and links have accessible names
- Focus visible on every focusable element
- Skip links on every page
- Live regions for the live activity feed (`aria-live="polite"`)
- Prefers-reduced-motion respected for animations

CI runs axe-core against key pages on every build.

## States every screen must have

Per ADR-029, design these BEFORE the happy path:

1. **Loading** — skeleton (matching the final layout's shape) or progress indicator. Never a blank screen.
2. **Empty** — context-aware copy ("No ambassadors yet — invite your first") + a primary action. Never just "No data."
3. **Error** — clear message, retry action, link to help if user-actionable, link to status page if not.
4. **Degraded** — banner when realtime is offline, integration is down, or data may be stale. Polling fallback.
5. **Happy path** — the default.

For ambassador screens, also design:
6. **Day-zero** — what the screen looks like for an ambassador with zero clicks, zero sales, zero rewards. Onboarding-shaped, not bare.

## Charts (Recharts)

- All charts use the Ravo theme via a shared `ChartContainer` component
- Tooltips show absolute values alongside percentages
- Dual-axis charts only when ADR-028's scaling rule is applied
- Empty states for "no data in this period" inside the chart frame
- Loading skeletons sized to match the final chart

## Number, money, date display

- All numbers via `formatNumber(value, locale)` — never raw string interpolation
- All money via `formatMoney({ amount_cents, currency }, locale)`
- All dates via `formatInFestivalTz(date, event, format)` for festival data, `formatInUserTz(date, user, format)` for personal data
- Lint rule blocks raw `toLocaleString`, `toFixed` in components

## Percentage comparison guards

Per ADR-027, always use the `comparePeriods` helper. Never compute `(current - prior) / prior * 100` inline.

## Mobile (ambassador app)

- Mobile-first breakpoints; design at 360px width baseline
- PWA manifest + service worker (Workbox)
- Installable (Add to Home Screen prompt after 2nd session)
- Native share sheet via `navigator.share` where available; fallback to copy-to-clipboard + per-platform deeplinks
- Push notifications via Web Push API (post-Phase 6 — needs HTTPS + service worker)
- Tap targets ≥ 44×44 px
- Sticky bottom nav for the 6 surfaces (Home, Share, Stats, Rewards, Community, Profile)

## Ambassador-specific UX rules

- **Leaderboard view:** show top 10 + the viewer's own position + gap to next rank. Never show absolute rank deep in the tail (ADR-023).
- **Stats framing:** cohort-relative wherever possible ("top 20% this week"), then personal trajectory ("3 sales away from your personal best"), then absolute (ADR-024).
- **Rewards view:** each reward shown as itself with its branding (collaboration label logo if set). Never aggregated. State badges (`pending`, `confirmed`, `fulfilled`, `reversed`) with timeline.
- **Share flow:** asset → tap → app generates link + caption + opens share sheet. Two taps maximum (ADR-025).

## Admin-specific UX rules

- **Sales Feed:** real-time stream, click any sale → trace view with attribution chain + reassign action
- **Reward fulfillment queue:** grouped by reward type; bulk-select for batch actions; clear "requires admin confirmation" badge on tier-4 cash items
- **Integration health:** persistent indicator in the sidebar/header showing provider connection status
- **Audit log:** filterable, exportable, never editable

## Never do

- Hardcode strings — use next-intl
- Hardcode colors — use CSS variables
- Hardcode separators or formats — use Intl helpers
- Show "Loading..." text — use skeletons
- Show "Error" with no action — give the user something to do
- Use placeholder text as a label
- Animate without checking prefers-reduced-motion
- Lock the user out of features without explaining why (e.g., "Connect Weeztix to enable this" with a link, not a grey button)
